21/07/2004
PARIS, France -- Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said Tuesday (20 July) that the government does not only want to achieve EU membership, but also aims to raise the country's standard of living. He added that even if not given an accession date this December, the government would continue to pursue measures needed to complete the Copenhagen political criteria. Speaking after meeting with French President Jacques Chirac, he said Turkey's reform process is ongoing and would continue in the future. (NTV - 21/07/04)
